IA%20bloc%20may%20get%2093-166.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpinion%20polls%20do%20get%20the%20direction%20right%20in%20most%20cases.%20However%2C%20their%20seat%20tally%20is%20known%20to%20be%20off%20the%20mark%20in%20several%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20is%20elections%202024%20a%20done%20deal%3F%20There%20are%20three%20factors%20that%20suggest%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Late%20Deciders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%2025%25%20to%2030%25%20of%20voters%20decide%20whom%20to%20vote%20for%20on%20the%20very%20day%20of%20voting%20or%20just%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20before%20polls%2C%20as%20per%20the%20National%20Elections%20Studies%20reports%20published%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20(CSDS)%20over%20the%20years.%20This%20means%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20voters%20who%20are%20indecisive%20till%20the%20very%20end%2C%20and%20they%20can%20swing%20the%20elections%20in%20any%20direction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2036%25%20voters%20know%20which%20party%20to%20back%20even%20before%20the%20campaign%20starts%3B%2012%25%20do%20so%20after%20candidates%20are%20announced%2C%20while%2018%25%20make%20up%20their%20minds%20during%20campaigns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Axis%20My%20India%202019%20exit%20poll%2C%20this%20number%20is%20even%20higher%20at%2043%25.%20Survey%20data%20underlines%20the%20significance%20of%20multi-phase%2C%20month-long%20poll%20campaigns.%20Some%2043%20per%20cent%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20made%20their%20final%20decision%20either%20on%20the%20day%20of%20polling%20(14%25)%20or%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2Fafter%20community%20meetings%20(29%25).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdisha%20(68%25)%2C%20Maharashtra%20(56%25)%2C%20Jharkhand%20(63%25)%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20(55%25)%2C%20Telangana%20(57%25)%2C%20Bihar%20(55%25)%20and%20West%20Bengal%20(50%25)%C2%A0are%20the%20top%20seven%20states%20with%20late%20deciders%20(figures%20in%20brackets%C2%A0are%20the%20percentages%20of%20such%20voters).%C2%A0All%20of%20them%2C%20except%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20have%20triangular%20or%20multi-cornered%20contests.%20Four%20states%20are%20from%20the%20East%2C%20and%20one%20each%20is%20from%20Central%2C%20South%20and%20Western%20zones.%20In%20all%20these%20states%2C%20at%20least%20half%20of%20the%20voters%20decide%20which%20party%20to%20back%20very%20late%20in%20the%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20A%20Small%20Number%20of%20Loyal%20Voters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2031%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20Axis%20My%20India%202019%20exit%20poll%20said%20they%20were%20loyal%20to%20only%20one%20party%20and%20backed%20it%20election%20after%20election.%20This%20indicates%20only%2031%25%20of%20people%20in%20the%20country%20are%20hardcore%2C%20ideologically%20aligned%20voters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20got%20an%2018.8%25%20vote%20share%2C%20lost%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20which%20netted%2028.6%25%20votes.%20This%20was%20the%20worst%20performance%20for%20the%20BJP%20since%201991.%20In%20contrast%2C%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20got%2019.7%25%20votes%20against%20the%20BJP's%2037.7%25.%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20was%20the%20Congress's%20worst%20performance%20ever.%20The%20combined%20bottomed-out%20or%20lowest%20vote%20share%20for%20both%20parties%20is%2038.5%25.%20Adjusting%20for%20the%20leadership%20factor%2C%20this%20almost%20matches%20the%20percentage%20of%20loyal%20voters%20as%20shown%20by%20the%20Axis%20poll.%20That%20is%2C%20it%20can%20be%20assumed%20that%20whoever%20is%20voting%20for%20the%20Congress%20today%20is%20mostly%20a%20loyal%20voter%2C%20just%20like%20whoever%20backed%20the%20losing%20BJP%20in%202009%20in%20its%20lost%20cause%20could%20safely%20be%20assumed%20to%20be%20its%20loyal%20or%20ideological%20supporter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20big%20(almost%2070%25)%20section%20of%20voters%20'swing'%2C%20that%20is%2C%20their%20preferences%20shift%20election%20to%20election.%20The%20remaining%2031%25%20are%20'loyal'%20ones%2C%20and%20this%C2%A0nearly%20matches%20the%20share%20of%20people%20-%2036%25%20-%20who%20decide%20whom%20to%20vote%20for%20even%20before%20the%20campaigns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20states%20where%20such%20loyal%20voters%20are%20high%20in%20numbers%20are%20Uttarakhand%C2%A0(60%25)%2C%20Gujarat%20(52%25)%2C%20Rajasthan%20(48%25)%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20(44%25)%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(44%25)%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(38%25)%2C%20Kerala%20(37%25)%20and%20Haryana%20(36%25).%20Figures%20in%20brackets%C2%A0denote%20the%20percentages%20of%20such%20voters.%20Five%20of%20these%20states%20witness%20largely%20bipolar%20contests%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%2C%20while%20Kerala%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20respectively%20witness%20a%20Congress%20vs%20Left%20contest%20and%20regional%20battles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Local%20Candidate%20Factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%2025%25%20of%20voters%20-%20the%20second-biggest%20group%20-%20the%20local%20candidate%20is%20the%20most%20important%20factor%20determining%20their%20choice%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Axis%20My%20India%20exit%20poll%202019.%20For%2037%25%2C%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%20was%20important%2C%2022%25%20focused%20on%20the%20party%20symbol%2C%203%25%20on%20manifesto%20promises%2C%20and%2013%25%20on%20other%20factors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20parties%20have%20not%20declared%20names%20for%20all%20seats%20yet%2C%20and%20hence%2C%20the%20'candidate'%20factor%20has%20not%20been%20taken%20into%20account%20by%20most%20early%20opinion%20polls.%20To%20reiterate%2C%20almost%2012%25%20of%20voters%20decide%20whom%20to%20vote%20for%20after%20the%20candidates%20are%20announced.%20And%20twenty-five%20per%20cent%20-%20the%20share%20of%20people%20who%20focus%20on%20local%20candidates%20-%20is%20a%20huge%20number%20as%20well%2C%20higher%20than%20the%20lead%20of%2018%25%20the%20BJP%20clinched%20over%20the%20Congress%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20Opinion%20Polls%20Have%20Gaps%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20while%20many%20early%20opinion%20polls%20tend%20to%20be%20directionally%20correct%2C%20their%20seat%20calculations%20can%20go%20wrong%20due%20to%20these%20factors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%202009%20elections%2C%20the%20UPA's%20best%20estimate%20was%20taken%20to%20be%20257%20seats%20as%20per%20an%20agency%2C%20and%20it%20got%20262%20seats.%20For%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20projection%20was%20144%2C%20but%20it%20ended%20up%20getting%20206.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202014%20elections%2C%20the%20NDA%20was%20expected%20to%20win%20in%20275%20constituencies%2C%20but%20it%20ultimately%20got%20336.%20The%20BJP%20got%20282%20seats%20against%20a%20projection%20of%20226%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20a%20projection%20for%20NDA%20pegged%20its%20seats%20at%20285%2C%20but%20it%20got%20353%20in%20the%20end.%20The%20BJP%20got%2065%20more%20than%20the%20projection%20of%20248%20for%20it%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20numbers%20and%20patterns%20should%20cheer%20both%20the%20supporters%20and%20opponents%20of%20the%20BJP.%20While%20the%20former%20could%20hope%20that%20the%20NDA%20will%20cross%20the%20400-mark%20given%20how%20opinion%20pollsters%20have%20underestimated%20it%20in%20the%20last%20two%20elections%2C%20the%20opposition%20could%20find%20some%20comfort%20in%20that%20old%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3Egame%20abhi%20baaki%20hai%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710492540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-04%2Fbjp-flag-afp-650_650x400_71493283316.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felection-2024-is-not-a-done-deal-three-voting-patterns-show-why-5243250%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20large%20number%20of%20late%20deciders%20and%20a%20small%20share%20of%20'loyal'%20voters%2C%20coupled%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20local%20candidates%2C%20can%20often%20alter%20the%20final%20outcome.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felection-2024-is-not-a-done-deal-three-voting-patterns-show-why-5243250%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felection-2024-is-not-a-done-deal-three-voting-patterns-show-why-5243250%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Felection-2024-is-not-a-done-deal-three-voting-patterns-show-why-5243250%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mid%20%26amp%3B%20small%20caps%20to%20correct%20further%3F%20Here's%20what%20you%20should%20know%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710492502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108519879%2Cimgsize-95736.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fmid-and-small-cap-stocks-to-correct-further-stocks-still-at-full-to-lofty-valuations%2Farticleshow%2F108517129.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20recent%20corrections%2C%20mid-cap%20and%20small-cap%20stocks%20are%20trading%20above%20their%20fundamental%20values%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20further%20decline.%20Kotak%20Institutional%20Equities%20highlights%20the%20market's%20uncertainty%20in%20shifting%20to%20fundamental%20values%20from%20sentiment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22