2Findiachina-border-deployments-risk-potential-armed-conflict-us-intel-report-101710400368779.html%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20released%20by%20the%20Director%20of%20National%20Intelligence%20(DNI)%2C%20underscored%20the%20strained%20relationship%20between%20India%20and%20China%2C%20citing%20sporadic%20encounters%20between%20their%20militaries%20as%20a%20risk%20for%20miscalculation%20and%20escalation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20shared%20disputed%20border%20between%20India%20and%20China%20will%20remain%20a%20strain%20on%20their%20bilateral%20relationship.%20While%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20not%20engaged%20in%20significant%20cross-border%20clashes%20since%202020%2C%20they%20are%20maintaining%20large%20troop%20deployments%2C%20and%20sporadic%20encounters%20between%20opposing%20forces%20risk%20miscalculation%20and%20escalation%20into%20armed%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Findiachina-border-deployments-risk-potential-armed-conflict-us-intel-report-101710400368779.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20pointed%20out%20China%E2%80%99s%20ambitions%20to%20establish%20overseas%20military%20bases%2C%20particularly%20in%20Sri%20Lanka%20and%20Pakistan.%20This%20move%20is%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20broader%20strategy%20to%20project%20power%20and%20safeguard%20its%20interests%20beyond%20its%20borders%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Findiachina-border-deployments-risk-potential-armed-conflict-us-intel-report-101710400368779.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%2C%20Pakistan%20and%20a%20fragile%20global%20order%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20calm%20persists%20following%20a%20cease-fire%20with%20Pakistan%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC)%20in%20early%202021%2C%20the%20report%20warns%20that%20any%20provocations%20from%20Islamabad%20could%20lead%20to%20armed%20conflict%20between%20the%20two%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20highlights%20the%20fragile%20global%20order%2C%20pointing%20to%20China%E2%80%99s%20military%20expansion%20plans%2C%20aggressive%20cyber%20operations%2C%20and%20potential%20interference%20in%20the%20upcoming%202024%20US%20presidential%20elections.%20Alongside%20these%20concerns%2C%20the%20assessment%20mentions%20ongoing%20conflicts%20such%20as%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20and%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia-China%20standoff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20India%20and%20China%20have%20amped%20up%20efforts%20on%20infrastructure%20projects%20near%20the%20border%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffresh-details-of-india-china-skirmishes-on-ladakh-border-emerge%5C%22%3Ea%20military%20standoff%20with%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Ladakh%20sector%20of%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%20began%20in%20May%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findia-china-ladakh-border-tension-explainer%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Two%20Steps%20Forward%2C%20One%20Step%20Back%E2%80%99%3A%20The%20Chequered%20Story%20of%20India%20and%20China%E2%80%99s%20Border%20Tensions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClose%20to%2050%2C000%20troops%20from%20each%20side%20have%20been%20stationed%20in%20the%20area%20and%20India%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20bilateral%20relations%20cannot%20be%20normalised%20till%20there%20is%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20in%20the%20border%20areas%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20continuation%20of%20these%20efforts%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20recently%20inaugurated%20the%20Sela%20tunnel%20in%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20enhancing%20all-weather%20connectivity%20to%20the%20strategically%20important%20region%20of%20Tawang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffresh-details-of-india-china-skirmishes-on-ladakh-border-emerge%5C%22%3Elost%20about%201%2C000%20square%20kilometres%20of%20area%20in%20Ladakh%20to%20Chinese%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%2C%20as%20per%20intelligence%20inputs%20provided%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%20Since%20then%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fladakh-india-china-breakthrough%5C%22%3Etwenty-eight%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fladakh-india-china-breakthrough%5C%22%3Erounds%20of%20negotiations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0between%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20failed%20to%20resolve%20the%20deadlock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20China%20has%20publicly%20staked%20their%20claim%20on%20parts%20of%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20renaming%20some%20towns%2C%20details%20about%20physical%20confrontation%20with%20Indian%20soldiers%20were%20never%20made%20public.%20Former%20chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%2C%20General%20M.M.%20Naravane%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffresh-details-of-india-china-skirmishes-on-ladakh-border-emerge%5C%22%3E%20memoirs%20were%20also%20withheld%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20revealing%20how%20the%20Modi%20government%20left%20the%20Army%20to%20its%20own%20devices%20when%20hostilities%20at%20Galwan%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710489642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F01125755%2FChina-india.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fus-intelligence-report-warns-of-potential-armed-conflict-between-india-and-china%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20underscored%20the%20strained%20relationship%20between%20India%20and%20China%20citing%20sporadic%20encounters%20between%20their%20militaries%20as%20a%20risk%20for%20miscalculation%20and%20e