toma%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Etold%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20tumours%20have%20returned%20but%20scientists%20are%20confident%20that%20with%20some%20tweaks%2C%20CAR-T%20will%20become%20beneficial%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20clearly%20made%20the%20tumours%20shrink%2C%20so%20it's%20doing%20something.%20Now%2C%20the%20hard%20part%20starts%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Brawley.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20drug%20that%20has%20some%20activity.%20We%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20we%20can%20maximise%20that%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencealert.com%2Fbreakthrough-therapy-obliterates-deadly-brain-tumor-in-days%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScience%20Alert%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20report%20that%20the%20therapy%20was%20used%20on%20a%2072-year-old%20patient%20and%20showed%20remarkable%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20CAR-T%2C%20a%20patient's%20own%20T-cells%20are%20collected%20and%20re-engineered%20to%20identify%20surface%20markers%20on%20the%20outside%20of%20cancer%20cells%20before%20being%20injected%20in%20the%20body%20again.%20It's%20like%20employing%20a%20local%20bounty%20hunter%20to%20slip%20silently%20through%20the%20alleys%20in%20search%20of%20a%20wanted%20villain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreclinical%20laboratory%20trials%20found%20the%20T-cell-engaging%20antibody%20molecule%20(TEAM)%20therapy%20worked%20as%20expected%20at%20the%20site%20of%20a%20tumour%2C%20even%20recruiting%20other%20regulatory%20T-cells%20to%20join%20in%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experiment%20was%20carried%20out%20on%20three%20patients%20and%20cancer%20returned%20in%20two%20patients%20-%20a%2074-year-old%20man%20and%2057-year-old%20woman.%20But%20the%2072-year-old%20participant%20showed%20no%20sign%20of%20cancer%20return%2C%20only%20some%20side%20effects%20like%20fever%20some%20nodules%20briefly%20appearing%20in%20lungs%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3EScience%20Alert%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20was%20published%20in%20The%20New%20England%20Journal%20of%20Medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710488280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2F9lq1qdao_brain-scan-generic-unsplash_625x300_30_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fbreakthrough-new-therapy-makes-deadly-brain-tumour-disappear-in-days-5242926%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Under%20CAR-T%2C%20a%20patient's%20own%20T-cells%20are%20collected%20and%20re-engineered%20to%20identify%20surface%20markers%20on%20the%20outside%20of%20cancer%20cells%20before%20being%20injected%20in%20the%20body%20again.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fbreakthrough-new-therapy-makes-deadly-brain-tumour-disappear-in-days-5242926%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fbreakthrough-new-therapy-makes-deadly-brain-tumour-disappear-in-days-5242926%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fbreakthrough-new-therapy-makes-deadly-brain-tumour-disappear-in-days-5242926%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Environmentalist%20Among%20Six%20Recipients%20of%20Planet%20Earth%20Awards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15123600%2Fimage-1960.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Indian%20environmentalist%20and%20former%20climate%20negotiator%20S.%20Faizi%20is%20one%20of%20the%20six%20recipients%20of%20the%202024%20Planet%20Earth%20Awards%2C%20instituted%20by%20the%20Alliance%20of%20World%20Scientists%2C%20an%20international%20body%20of%20scientists%20based%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizi%2C%20who%20hails%20from%20Kerala%2C%20has%20received%20the%20award%20for%20his%20contributions%20to%20forest%20conservation%2C%20biodiversity%20research%20and%20support%20of%20indigenous%20rights%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20award%20%E2%80%9Cacknowledges%20individuals%20who%20champion%20life%20on%20Earth%E2%80%9D%20and%20those%20who%20%E2%80%9Cdemonstrate%20exceptional%20creativity%20or%20contributions%20in%20their%20work%20in%20science-based%20advocacy%20with%20the%20public%2C%20policymakers%2C%20or%20other%20non-scientist%20groups%20seeking%20solutions%20to%20environmental%20challenges%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Alliance%20of%20World%20Scientists%20is%20a%20new%20body%20of%20around%2027%2C000%20scientists%20across%20180%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Ripple%20is%20AWS%E2%80%99s%20director.%20He%20is%20a%20scientist%20at%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20Conservation%20Biology%20Institute%20and%20Distinguished%20Professor%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University.%20Ripple%20was%20the%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20communication%20%E2%80%93%20endorsed%20by%2015%2C364%20scientists%20from%20184%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20titled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbioscience%2Farticle%2F67%2F12%2F1026%2F4605229%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EGlobal%20Scientists%E2%80%99%20Warning%20to%20Humanity%3A%20A%20second%20Notice%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017%20that%20warned%20that%20people%20had%20to%20practice%20environmentally%20sustainable%20alternatives%20to%20counter%20catastrophic%20biodiversity%20loss%20and%20other%20drastic%20impacts%20on%20the%20natural%20world%20due%20to%20human%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDr.%20Faizi%E2%80%99s%20accomplishments%20include%20important%20contributions%20to%20landmark%20global%20events%20such%20as%20the%20UN%20Conference%20on%20Environment%20and%20Development%20(Earth%20Summit)%20and%20the%20Convention%20on%20Biological%20Diversity%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20AWS%20award%20site%20notes.%20%E2%80%9CHis%20efforts%20have%20ranged%20from%20advocating%20for%20national%20sovereignty%20over%20biodiversity%20to%20proposing%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20UN%20Environmental%20Security%20Council.%20More%20recently%2C%20this%20former%20anti-Apartheid%20activist%20has%20campaigned%20for%20nuclear%20disarmament%20and%20democratising%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AWS%20also%20acknowledged%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpivotal%20role%E2%80%9D%20Faizi%20played%20%E2%80%9Cin%20articulating%20the%20global%20South%E2%80%99s%20stance%20on%20key%20environment%20and%20development%20issues%2C%20often%20overcoming%20opposition%20from%20Western%20negotiators%20at%20UN%20environmental%20conferences%E2%80%9D%20during%20his%20work%20as%20a%20climate%20negotiator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20recipients%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20award%20include%20US%20climate%20scientist%20James%20Hansen%2C%20environmental%20policy%20specialist%20Denise%20Margaret%20S.%20Matias%20of%20the%20Philippines%2C%20Swedish%20sustainability%20scientist%20Kimberly%20Nicholas%2C%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20freshwater%20conservationist%20Jamie%20Pittock%20and%20biologist%20Fernando%20Valladares%20of%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20Planet%20Earth%20Award%20recipients%20provide%20compelling%20examples%20of%20how%20scientists%20can%20engage%20in%20effective%20science-based%20advocacy%20to%20help%20address%20important%20environmental%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ripple%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20hope%20they%20will%20inspire%20others%20to%20act%20in%20this%20regard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fi%3EAathira%20%3Cspan%20tabindex%3D%5C%22-1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-hovercard-id%3D%5C%22aathira%40thewire.in%5C%22%20data-hovercard-owner-id%3D%5C%22108%5C%22%3EPerinchery%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3Ecaught%20up%20with%20Dr.%20S.%20Faizi%20for%20a%20brief%20email%20interview%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20his%20award.%20Below%20are%20the%20excerpts%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAathira%3A%20How%20does%20it%20feel%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20six%20recipients%20of%20the%202024%20Planet%20Earth%20Awards%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaizi%3A%20I%20am%20happy%20about%20the%20recognition%20by%20the%20scientific%20peers%2C%20although%20awards%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20much%20sense%20to%20me%20past%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAs%20an%20environmental%20scientist%20and%20activist%20working%20on%20numerous%20aspects%20of%20conservation%20for%20more%20than%20three%20decades%20now%2C%20what%20is%20the%20biggest%20concern%20or%20challenge%20pertaining%20to%20the%20environment%20in%20India%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20single%20most%20concern%20I%20have%20is%20about%20the%20alienation%20of%20the%20Adivasi%20community%20who%20have%20been%20the%20historical%20caretakers%20of%20our%20forests%20and%20wildlife%20from%20their%20traditional%20resource%20base.%20They%20could%20manage%20our%20forests%20and%20wildlife%20better%20than%20the%20hugely%20costly%20forest%20bureaucracy%20presiding%20over%20the%20loss%20of%20biodiversity.%20The%20good%20forests%20in%20India%20we%20have%20are%20still%20in%20the%20169%20Adivasi%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIn%20this%20era%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20consumerism%20and%20the%20unparalleled%20imbalance%20of%20power%20and%20influence%20of%20the%20rich%20and%20corporates%2C%20is%20there%20still%20hope%20for%20India%20to%20get%20onto%20a%20trajectory%20of%20sustainable%20development%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20say.%20The%20caste%20system%20has%20left%20us%20with%20a%20minority%20of%20affluence%20that%20surpasses%20the%20extreme%20form%20of%20western%20affluence%20and%20the%20massive%20majority%20living%20in%20poverty%20and%20destitution%2C%20with%20the%20poor%20outnumbering%20the%20poor%20in%20all%20African%20countries%20put%20together.%20This%20reign%20of%20inequality%20and%20injustice%20makes%20the%20pursuit%20of%20sustai