ia-news%2Flatest-news-live-live-news-today-pm-narendra-modi-bjp-lok-sabha-list-bjp-candidates-list-sbi-electoral-bonds-details-donor-list-future-gaming-and-hotel-services-electoral-bonds-congress-124031500107_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Flatest-news-live-live-news-today-pm-narendra-modi-bjp-lok-sabha-list-bjp-candidates-list-sbi-electoral-bonds-details-donor-list-future-gaming-and-hotel-services-electoral-bonds-congress-124031500107_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Flatest-news-live-live-news-today-pm-narendra-modi-bjp-lok-sabha-list-bjp-candidates-list-sbi-electoral-bonds-details-donor-list-future-gaming-and-hotel-services-electoral-bonds-congress-124031500107_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Chief%20On%20Why%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Disclosure%20Is%20Not%20Ideal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20All%20India%20Bar%20Association%20(AIBA)%20has%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20requesting%20a%20suo%20motu%20review%20of%20the%20Judgment%20passed%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20only%20qua%20issue%20of%20disclosure%20of%20identity%20of%20donors%20and%20their%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAIBA%20Chairman%20Dr%20Adish%20Aggarwala%20who%20is%20also%20the%20President%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20(SCBA)%20and%20former%20Vice-Chairman%20of%20the%20Bar%20Council%20of%20India%20(BCI)%20stated%20that%20revealing%20the%20names%20of%20corporate%20donors%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20donations%20would%20render%20the%20corporates%20vulnerable%20for%20victimisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibility%20of%20them%20being%20singled%20out%20by%20those%20parties%2C%20that%20had%20received%20less%20or%20no%20contribution%20from%20them%2C%20and%20further%20harassment%2C%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20if%20the%20names%20of%20corporate%20donors%20and%20their%20quantum%20of%20donation%20to%20various%20parties%20are%20revealed.%20This%20will%20be%20reneging%20on%20the%20promise%20given%20to%20them%20while%20accepting%20their%20voluntary%20donation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20submitted%20that%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20donation%2C%20the%20corporate%20donor%20was%20fully%20aware%20that%20after%20the%20donation%2C%20its%20identity%2C%20amount%20of%20donation%20and%20particulars%20of%20donee%20political%20party%2C%20would%20not%20be%20made%20public%20and%20would%20be%20kept%20confidential.%20This%20provision%20of%20secrecy%20was%20made%20in%20the%20relevant%20Scheme%20with%20the%20purpose%20that%20the%20donor%20will%20be%20not%20subject%20to%20victimization%20by%20any%20other%20political%20party%20to%20whom%20the%20donor%20has%20not%20donated%20under%20the%20Scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20regard%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%20Dr%20Adish%20Aggarwala%20apprised%20the%20five%20judges%20Bench%20about%20his%20letter%20addressed%20to%20CJI.%20The%20Chief%20Justice%20Dr%20DY%20Chandrachud%20asked%20Advocate%20Aggarwala%20to%20mention%20the%20matter%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdish%20Aggarwala%20through%20a%20letter%20stated%20that%20as%20per%20Article%20145(3)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20there%20should%20be%20at%20least%20five%20judges%20to%20hear%20cases%20that%20involve%20%26quot%3Ba%20substantial%20question%20of%20law%20as%20to%20the%20interpretation%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20or%20any%20reference%20under%20Article%20143%2C%20which%20deals%20with%20the%20power%20of%20the%20President%20of%20India%20to%20consult%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20But%20in%20the%20Writ%20Petition%20(C)%20No.%20880%20of%202017%20(and%20other%20connected%20matters)%2C%20while%20referring%20the%20case%20to%20the%20Constitution%20Bench%2C%20the%20substantial%20questions%20of%20law%20as%20to%20the%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Constitution%20were%20not%20framed%20in%20the%20reference%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20two%20questions%20of%20law%20were%20framed%20by%20the%20Constitution%20Bench%20while%20delivering%20the%20Judgment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ea.%20Whether%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20as%20envisaged%20by%20the%20amendment%20to%20Section%20182(1)%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%20infringes%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20violates%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%3B%20and%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eb.%20Whether%20the%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20voluntary%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%20under%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20and%20the%20amendments%20to%20Section%2029C%20of%20the%20RPA%2C%20Section%20182(3)%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%20and%20Section%2013A(b)%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%20are%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20citizens%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20raised%20by%20me%20does%20not%20get%20covered%20in%20the%20aforesaid%20two%20issues%20framed%20and%20decided%20by%20the%20Constitutional%20Bench%20and%20thus%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20review%20the%20Judgment%20on%20the%20points%20raised%20by%20me%20in%20the%20present%20letter%2C%20stated%20Adish%20Aggarwala.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710486480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-02%2Fa1ooga8_supreme-court-of-india_650x400_14_February_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-bar-chief-writes-to-chief-justice-why-electoral-bonds-disclosure-is-not-ideal-5242654%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20All%20India%20Bar%20Association%20has%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20r