104041291.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Es%205%2C400%20crore%20in%20Mongolia%3C%2Fa%3E%20(the%20Mongol%20Refinery%20Project%20is%20a%20government%20to%20government%20initiative)%20in%20September%2C%20two%20separate%20packages%20to%20build%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Fmegha-engineering-beats-lt-to-bag-rs14400-crore-thane-borivali-twin-tunnel-project-mmrda-head-10575341.html%5C%22%3E%20Thane-Borivali%20twin%20tunnel%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Mumbai%20for%20a%20total%20bid%20of%20Rs%2014%2C400%20crore%20in%20May%20and%20and%20a%20Rs%20500-crore%20order%20from%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fmeil-group-company-bags-rs-500-crore-order-from-defence-ministry-123061501190_1.html%5C%22%3E%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20its%20company%20IComm%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20working%20on%20the%20Zojila%20tunnel%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20according%20to%20its%20website%2C%20which%20also%20lists%20key%20projects%20like%20the%20Char%20Dham%20Rail%20Tunnel%2C%20six%20Laning%20of%20Vijayawada%20bypass%2C%20Delhi-Amritsar-Katra%20Expressway%2C%20Maharashtra%20Samruddhi%20Mahamarg%2C%20Solapur%20%E2%80%93%20Kurnool%20%E2%80%93%20Chennai%20Economic%20Corridor%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%E2%80%99s%20Western%20UP%20Power%20Transmission%20Company%20Limited%2C%20has%20also%20donated%20Rs%20220%20crores%20in%20electoral%20bonds-the%20seventh%20highest%20on%20the%20list%20published%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2012%2C%202019%2C%20the%20income%20tax%20department%20had%20conducted%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinspection%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20offices%20in%20Hyderabad%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fi-t-officials-inspect-meils-hyderabad-office%2Farticle29659393.ece%5C%22%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20company%2C%20however%2C%20denied%20that%20it%20was%20a%20raid%20or%20a%20search%20and%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Croutine%20inspection.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Income%20Tax%20Department%20has%20inspected%20our%20office%20on%20Friday.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20raid%20or%20search%2C%20but%20a%20routine%20inspection%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20company%20statement%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fcrime%2F080124%2Fklis-a-cesspool-of-corruption-cag-finds-excess-payments-of-rs7500-c.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Deccan%20Chronicle%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20a%20CAG%20audit%20report%20which%20made%20allegations%20against%20Megha%20for%20the%20work%20it%20had%20done%20in%20a%20major%20irrigation%20project%20in%20Telanganaa%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHigh-profile%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20(MEIL)%20has%20allegedly%20pocketed%20thousands%20of%20crores%20of%20rupees%20of%20public%20money%20in%20the%20ill-famed%20Kaleshwaram%20Lift%20Irrigation%20Scheme%20(KLIS)%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20patronage%20it%20enjoyed%20from%20the%20previous%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20government.%20According%20to%20the%20draft%20performance%20audit%20report%20on%20KLIS%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%2C%20the%20company%20was%20paid%20an%20excess%20of%20Rs.5%2C188.43%20crore%20in%20just%20four%20packages%2C%20involving%20the%20supply%20and%20commissioning%20of%20pumps%2C%20motors%20and%20auxiliary%20equipment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fnews%2Ftnm-nl-investigation-30-firms-facing-ed-it-probe-donated-rs-335-cr-to-bjp%5C%22%3E%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20News%20Minute%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ENewslaundry%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20also%20found%20that%2030%20firms%20that%20are%20facing%20ED%20and%20IT%20probes%20donated%20Rs%20335%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F17159848%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F17159848%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F17159848%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChennai%20Greenwoods%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20little%20known%20construction%20firm%20is%20in%20the.%20top%2020%20donors%2C%20having%20bought%20Rs%20105%20crore%20worth%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%20The%20firm%20is%20owned%20by%20the%20Andhra%20based%20Ramky%20group.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fin-other-news%2F090721%2Fit-raid-on-ramky-group-detects-artificial-loss-of-rs-1200cr.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20July%202021%2C%20Ramky%20was%20raided%20by%20the%20Income%20Tax%20authorities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20IT%20officials%20found%20many%20incriminating%20documents%20and%20loose%20sheets%20and%20seized%20them.%20These%20indicated%20involvement%20of%20the%20group%20in%20unaccounted%20transactions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20IT%20department%20said.%20Ramky%2C%20which%20was%20accused%20of%20having%20unaccounted%20income%20of%20Rs%20300%20crore%2C%20bought%20its%20first%20electoral%20bonds%20through%20Chennai%20Greenwoods%20in%20January%202022%2C%20making%20additional%20purchases%20in%20April%202022%20and%20again%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EQwik%20Supply%20Chain%20Private%20Limited%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20Mumbai-based%20company%20which%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20410%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20company%20information%20available%20on%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zaubacorp.com%2Fcompany%2FQWIK-SUPPLY-CHAIN-PRIVATE-LIMITED%2FU51100MH2000PTC129528%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3EZauba%20Corp%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20was%20founded%2023%20years%20ago%20in%202000.%20As%20per%20the%20data%20uploaded%20on%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20website%2C%20Qwik%20Supply%20Chain%2C%20a%20firm%20linked%20to%20Reliance%20group%2C%20made%20its%20first%20purchase%20of%20bonds%20on%20January%205%2C%202022.%20The%20second%20batch%20of%20purchases%20continued%20five%20days%20later%2C%20on%20January%2010.%20The%20purchase%20then%20followed%20on%20November%2011%2C%202022%20and%20a%20year%20later%20on%20November%2017%2C%202023.%20All%20electoral%20bond%20purchases%20were%20made%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%E2%80%99s%20two%20present%20directors%20are%20Vipul%20Pranlal%20Mehta%20and%20Tapas%20Mitra.%20According%20to%20%3Ci%3EZauba%20Corp%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20Tapas%20Mitra%2C%20is%20also%20the%20director%20of%20Reliance%20Oil%20and%20Petroleum%2C%20Reliance%20Eros%20Productions%2C%20Reliance%20Photo%20Films%2C%20Reliance%20Fire%20Brigades%2C%20Ral%20Investment%20Private%20Limited%2C%20Reliance%20First%20Private%20Limited%2C%20Reliance%20Polyester%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202021-2022%2C%20Mitra%E2%80%99s%20salary%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwhole-time%20director%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20company%20was%20Rs%2046.1%20lakh%2C%20along%20with%20additional%20perks%20worth%20Rs%203.53%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20according%20to%20details%20uploaded%20on%20Zauba%20Corp%2C%20shows%20that%20they%20have%20an%20office%20space%20in%20Dhobi%20Talao%2C%20in%20South%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffcplweb.co.in%2FHome%2Fabout%5C%22%3Ecompany%E2%80%99s%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Quick%20Supply%20Chain%20Private%20Limited%20is%20engaged%20in%20business%20of%20providing%20logistics%20and%20other%20support%20services%20to%20its%20Customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%E2%80%99s%20returns%20and%20shareholder%20details%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202022-23%20attributes%20major%20turnover%20(91.1%25)%20to%20land%20transport%2C%20the%20remaining%208.3%25%20came%20from%20providing%20support%20service%20to%20other%20organisations%20and%20a%20minuscule%20share%20was%20of%20wholesale%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHaldia%20Energy%20Limited%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20biggest%20donor%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20Sanjeev%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20Haldia%20Energy%20Limited%20that%20donated%20Rs%20377%20crore%20between%20October%201%2C%202019%20and%20January%205%2C%202024.%20The%20Kolkata-based%20billionaire%20owns%20the%20RP-Sanjeev%20Goenka%20group%20that%20has%20businesses%20in%20sectors%20like%20power%20and%20energy%2C%20retail%2C%20IT%2C%20FMCG%2C%20media%20and%20entertainment%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Haldia%20Energy%20Limited%20also%20runs%20a%20coal-based%20thermal%20power%20plant%20in%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20port%20township%20Haldia%20and%20is%20a%20wholly%20owned%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20Calcutta%20Electric%20Supply%20Corporation%2C%20a%20flagship%20company%20of%20the%20RP-Sanjeev%20Goenka%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20began%20purchasing%20electoral%20bonds%20on%20October%201%2C%202019%20when%20it%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%201%20crore.%20However%2C%20then%20the%20purchasing%20became%20more%20frequent%20each%20subsequent%20year%2C%20even%20as%20the%20donations%20kept%20increasing.%20The%20company%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2021%20crore%20in%202020%20in%20three%20tranches%2C%20and%20spent%20Rs%20105%20crore%20in%202021%20in%20five%20tranches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20it%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2085%20crore%20in%202022%2C%20while%20in%202023%20it%20spent%20Rs%20115%20crore%20in%20electoral%20bonds.%20Its%20last%20purchase%20was%20on%20January%205%2C%202024%20when%20it%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2035%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaldia%20bought%20its%20first%20bond%20on%20May%207%2C%202019%20of%2024%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2014%20crore%20(1%20crore%20each)%20and%201%20crore%20through%20ten%20bonds%2C%20each%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20denomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20company%20owned%20by%20Goenka%2C%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure%20Ltd.%20bought%20Rs%20115%20crore%20worth%20of%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20West%20Bengal%20BJP%20leader%20Suvendu%20Adhikari%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanchronicle.com%2Fnation%2Fin-other-news%2F231123%2Fsuvendu-targets-sanjiv-goenka-on-funding-tmc.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20targeted%20Sanjeev%20Goenka%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20funding%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20other%20modes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoenka%2C%20who%20also%20owns%20the%20IPL%20team%20Lucknow%20Super%20Giants%20and%20Kolkata-based%20ISL%20football%20club%20Mohun%20Bagan%20Super%20Giant%2C%20has%20been%20expanding%20his%20businesses%20even%20in%20the%20north-eastern%20states%20where%20he%20had%20planned%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20renewable%20energy%20sector.%20His%20company%20officials%20had%20a%20meeting%20with%20the%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20development%20of%20the%20north-eastern%20region%2C%20B.L.Verma%2C%20in%20which%20they%20had%20expressed%20their%20interests%20in%20developing%20a%20few%20hydro-power%20projects%20in%20the%20north-eastern%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CESC%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Frenewables%2Frp-sanjiv-goenka-group-to-explore-ne-states-for-renewable-energy-project%2Farticleshow%2F107859433.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ebeen%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%20interests%20in%20solar%20power%20generation%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Gujarat%20where%20it%20was%20looking%20to%20acquire%20over%2050%2C000%20acres%20of%20land%20for%20its%20proposed%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%202024%2C%20the%20CESC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fcesc-forays-into-green-hydrogen-domain%2Farticleshow%2F106681920.cms%5C%22%3Eoutbid%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20ACME%20Cleantech%2C%20Sembcorp%2C%20Greenko%2C%20Avaada%2C%20Reliance%20Industries%2C%20JSW%20Energy%2C%20and%20the%20Adani%20group%20to%20establish%20a%2010%2C500-tonne%20per%20annum%20green%20hydrogen%20production%20facility.%20The%20tender%20was%20invited%20by%20the%20Solar%20Energy%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjeev%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20CESC%20and%20RPG%20Enterprises%20has%20been%20under%20the%20CBI%20scanner%20since%202012%20in%20a%20case%20related%20to%20corruption%2C%20cheating%2C%20and%20criminal%20conspiracy%20over%20the%20allocation%20of%20coal%20blocks%20in%20Deocha%20Pachami%2C%20Tara%20West%2C%20Mahan%20and%20South%20Dadhu%20during%201993-95.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EVedanta%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVedanta%20is%20the%20fifth%20largest%20buyer%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%20It%20was%20also%20in%20the%20news%20when%20the%20controversial%20method%20of%20the%20finance%20bill%20was%20used%20to%20introduce%20electoral%20bonds.%20It%20was%20around%20the%20same%20time%20that%20a%20money%20Bill%2C%20involving%20Vedanta%2C%20was%20deployed%20to%20amend%20the%20FCRA%20retrospectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20made%20crucial%20amendments%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Contributions%20Regulation%20Act%20(FCRA)%20to%20legalise%20Vedanta%E2%80%99s%20donations%20to%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress.%20These%20amendments%20were%20enacted%20as%20a%20one-off%2C%20retrospective%20amendment%20to%20the%20FCRA%2C%20exempting%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20from%20violating%20Section%203%20of%20the%20Act.%20This%20section%20prohibits%20political%20parties%2C%20their%20office-bearers%2C%20and%20members%20of%20any%20House%20from%20receiving%20contributions%20from%20foreign%20companies%20or%20companies%20in%20India%20controlled%20by%20foreign%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVedanta%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20375.65%20crore.%20On%20January%2010%2C%202022%2C%20it%20bought%2073%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%201%20crore%20each.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-puts-12-billion-price-tag-to-acquire-bpcl-11642070967927.html%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3ELivemint%3C%2Fi%3E%20reported%20on%20January%2014%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20the%20Vedanta%20Group%20made%20a%20bid%20to%20buy%20Bharat%20Petroleum%20Corporation%20Ltd%20(BPCL)%20or%20BPCL%2C%20as%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cwilling%20to%20spend%20%2412%20billion%20to%20acquire%20India%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20refiner%20Bharat%20Petroleum%20Corp.%2C%20an%20asset%20sale%20that%E2%80%99s%20among%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20and%20which%20has%20faced%20delays%20in%20completion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBillionaire%20chairman%20Anil%20Agarwal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Foil-gas%2Fvedanta-puts-12-billion-price-tag-on-bharat-petroleum%2Farticleshow%2F88876066.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ewas%20quoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20saying%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20bid%20aggressively%2C%20but%20we%20will%20put%20the%20right%20price.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20market%20cap%20of%20the%20company%20is%20about%20%2411%20billion%20to%20%2412%20billion%2C%20so%20this%20is%20the%20amount%20of%20investment%20we%E2%80%99re%20looking%20at.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHad%20this%20disinvestment%20gone%20through%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20privatisation%20exercises%2C%20but%20it%20was%20called%20off%2C%20as%20two%20of%20the%20three%20companies%20that%20had%20shown%20interest%20in%20acquiring%20the%20public%20sector%20undertaking%20withdrew%20their%20bids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgarwal%20told%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fgovernment-has-withdrawn-bpcl-divestment-offer-will-come-back-with-a-revised-plan-anil-agarwal-8395891.html%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3EMoneycontrol%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20April%2022%20that%20the%20government%20has%20withdrawn%20the%20offer%20to%20sell%20its%20stake%20in%20BPCL%20and%20will%20come%20up%20with%20a%20new%20strategy.%20Next%20only%20to%20Indian%20Oil%2C%20BPCL%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20second-largest%20oil%20marketing%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20interesting%20point%20was%20made%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20founding%20editor%20M.K.%20Venu.%20%E2%80%9CInteresting%20that%20Vedanta%20group%20donated%20bonds%20while%20it%20was%20under%20scrutiny%20by%20ED%2FCBI%20through%202019%20to%202022.%20Around%20this%20time%20the%20group%20was%20also%20chosen%20for%20PM%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ambitious%20semiconductor%20project%20in%20Gujarat%20for%20which%20the%20government%20proposed%20a%20massive%20grant%20of%20%245%20billion.%20Project%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fructify%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710446924000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ftop-electoral-bond-purchasers-include-some-companies-that-were-raided-or-under-the-scanner%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Other%20big%20donors%20include%20Vedanta%2C%20a%20company%20related%20to%20Reliance%2C%20and%20companies%20run%20by%20Sanjiv%20Goenka.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jamaican%20dancehall%20star%20wins%20appeal%20against%20murder%20c