%20a%20nine-year%20high%20for%20the%20country%2C%20and%20come%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20However%2C%20subsidies%20for%20renewable%20energy%20made%20up%20only%2010%25%20of%20this%20amount.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20socially%20responsible%20manner%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20or%20ensuring%20a%20just%20transition%20%E2%80%93%20will%20be%20important%20for%20India%20to%20achieve%20its%20global%20commitments%20such%20as%20achieving%2050%25%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20sources%20by%202030%2C%20energy%20independence%20by%202047%2C%20and%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%202070%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFossil%20fuel%20subsidies%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iisd.org%2Fstory%2Fmapping-india-energy-policy-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMapping%20India%E2%80%99s%20Energy%20Policy%3A%20A%20Decade%20in%20Action%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20shows%20that%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20show%20an%20interesting%20pattern.%20In%20what%20could%20be%20a%20good%20sign%2C%20it%20has%20declined%20by%2059%25%20since%202014%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Can%20accomplishment%20that%20many%20other%20large%20economies%20have%20struggled%20to%20achieve%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20finer%20details%20tell%20a%20slightly%20different%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202022%20energy%20crisis%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20and%20the%20increasing%20demand%20for%20power%20in%20India%20have%20caused%20the%20country%20to%20encourage%20%E2%80%9Call%20forms%20of%20energy%20supplies%20and%20adopt%20a%20mixed%20approach%20to%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20clean%20energy%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20figures%20from%20the%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20also%20show%20that%20coal%20accounts%20for%2045%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20primary%20energy%20supply%20in%202022%2C%20up%20from%2043%25%20in%202020.%20Altogether%2C%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20were%20five%20times%20greater%20than%20clean%20energy%20subsidies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20fiscal%20year%202023%20alone%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20subsidies%20rose%20at%20least%20Rs%2070%2C692%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20staggering%2063%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year.%20Coal%20subsidies%20reached%20almost%20Rs%2050%2C000%20crore%20in%20FY%202023%3A%20but%20this%20is%20only%20a%2017%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20FY%202022.%20The%20central%20government%20provided%20at%20least%20ten%20different%20subsidies%20to%20coal%2C%20but%20the%20largest%20in%202023%20were%20tax%20expenditures%20(concessional%20custom%20duty%20on%20imported%20coal%20and%20a%20concessional%20GST%20rate).%20To%20meet%20its%20rising%20energy%20demands%2C%20India%20also%20relied%20a%20lot%20on%20coal%20imports%20in%202023.%20Non-coking%20coal%20imports%20rose%20by%2020%25%20by%20volume%20that%20year.%20As%20per%20the%20report%2C%20this%20is%20the%20highest%20growth%20in%20non-coking%20coal%20imports%20since%202015.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20consumer%20price%20support%20for%20electricity%20still%20continues%20to%20grow%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%20It%20was%20the%20single%20largest%20subsidy%20mechanism%20in%202023%2C%20accounting%20for%2050%25%20of%20all%20energy%20subsidies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20have%20reduced%20by%2059%25%20since%20their%20peak%20in%202013-14%2C%20without%20further%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etargeting%20and%20a%20return%20to%20a%20market-based%20pricing%20regime%2C%20they%20could%20mount%20again%2C%20resulting%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebudgetary%20impacts%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20co-author%20of%20the%20report%20Swasti%20Raizada%2C%20policy%20advisor%20at%20IISD.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20undesirable%20as%20untargeted%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20are%20an%20inefficient%20way%20of%20supporting%20low-income%20households%2C%20and%20they%20shrink%20the%20fiscal%20space%20available%20for%20supporting%20clean%20energy%20technologies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raizada%20added%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERenewable%20energy%20and%20EVs%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202023%2C%20both%20clean%20energy%20and%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%20grew%20by%20around%2040%25%20with%20subsidies%20for%20renewable%20energy%20and%20electric%20vehicles%20growing%20slightly%20faster.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20renewable%20energy%20subsidies%20increased%20to%20Rs%2014%2C843%20crore%2C%20an%208%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20FY%202022.%20These%20subsidies%2C%20however%2C%20still%20remain%20fairly%20low%20when%20compared%20to%20that%20afforded%20to%20fossil%20fuels%20during%20this%20time.%20The%20clean%20energy%20subsidies%20accounted%20for%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20total%20energy%20subsidies%2C%20while%20subsidies%20for%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%20contributed%20around%2040%25.%20The%20majority%20of%20the%20remaining%20subsidies%20were%20for%20electricity%20consumption%2C%20particularly%20in%20agriculture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COngoing%20high%20levels%20of%20public%20financial%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuels%20not%20only%20undermine%20emission%20reduction%20goals%20but%20also%20perpetuate%20dependence%20on%20price-volatile%20and%20geopolitically%20risky%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20which%20weakens%20energy%20security%20and%20affordability%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Finvestment-of-2-trillion-per-year-needed-to-meet-global-2030-renewable-energy-target%5C%22%3EInvestment%20of%20%242%20Trillion%20Per%20Year%20Needed%20to%20Meet%20Global%202030%20Renewable%20Energy%20Target%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20added%20in%20the%20report%3A%20%E2%80%9CShifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20in%20a%20socially%20responsible%20manner%20provides%20a%20long-term%20solution%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20objectives%20and%20is%20consistent%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20achieving%2050%25%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20sources%20by%202030%2C%20energy%20independence%20by%202047%2C%20and%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%202070.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20field%20in%20which%20India%20needs%20to%20improve%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report%2C%20is%20in%20subsidies%20being%20offered%20for%20electric%20vehicles%20(EVs).%20While%20subsidies%20for%20EVs%20reached%20an%20all-time%20high%20in%202023%20at%20Rs%209%2C798%20crore%2C%20and%20India%20emerged%20as%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20markets%20for%20EVs%2C%20the%20report%20recommends%20that%20EVs%20be%20%E2%80%9Cwider%20government%20support%E2%80%9D%20for%20%E2%80%9Cbusiness%20continuity%20and%20promoting%20further%20investments%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20it%C2%A0%20comes%20to%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20also%20needs%20to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20cost-benefit%20analysis%20to%20allocate%20a%20portion%20of%20its%20energy%20revenues%20to%20meet%20its%20just%20transition%20needs%2C%20where%20the%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20are%20replaced%20with%20renewable%20and%20clean%20energy%20options%20while%20also%20helping%20communities%20dependent%20on%20fossil%20fuel-based%20livelihood%20measures%20transition%20gradually.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHigher%20taxes%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20will%20also%20help%20the%20country%2C%20and%20the%20revenues%20that%20come%20from%20this%20can%20be%20used%20to%20support%20economically%20backward%20communities%2C%20the%20report%20mentioned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPrevious%20studies%20show%20that%20India%20will%20require%20significant%20investment%20to%20make%20its%20energy%20transition%20just%2C%20sustainable%2C%20and%20inclusive%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Deepak%20Sharma%2C%20policy%20analyst%20at%20IISD%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20state-owned%20enterprises%20will%20be%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20this%20shift.%20As%20their%20majority%20shareholder%2C%20the%20government%20should%20ensure%20that%20all%20fresh%20capital%20going%20to%20these%20entities%20is%20linked%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20net%20zero%20commitments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710430233000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F14090239%2Fred-zeppelin-UVGE-o757-g-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Findias-energy-subsidies-high-fossil-fuel-subsidies-more-than-renewables%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shifting%20support%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20clean%20energy%20while%20also%20ensuring%20a%20just%20transition%20will%20be%20important%20for%20India%20to%20achieve%20its%20commitments%20towards%20attaining%20net-zero%2C%20the%20report%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Findias-energy-subsidies-high-fossil-fuel-subsidies-more-than-renewables%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Uploads%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Data%2C%20No%20Info%20on%20Who%20Paid%20Whom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20day%20before%20its%20court-ordered%20deadline%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20has%20uploaded%20data%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20and%20encashed%20since%202019%20onto%20its%20website%2C%20it%20said%20in%20a%20press%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20provided%20it%20the%20data%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20press%20note%2C%20the%20ECI%20said%20it%20uploaded%20the%20data%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20and%20%E2%80%9Cas%20received%20from%20%5Bthe%5D%20SBI%20on%20%5Ban%5D%20%E2%80%98as%20is%20where%20is%E2%80%99%20basis%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20had%20made%20this%20data%20available%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fcandidate-politicalparty%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fcandidate-politicalparty%3C%2Fa%3E%20URL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20may%20be%20recalled%20that%20in%20the%20said%20matter%2C%20ECI%20has%20consistently%20and%20categorically%20weighed%20in%20favour%20of%20disclosure%20and%20transparency%2C%20a%20position%20reflected%20in%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20noted%20in%20the%20order%20also%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ECI%20continued%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20bonds%20are%20interest-free%20financial%20instruments%20that%20individuals%20or%20groups%20may%20buy%20to%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Ein%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20the%20bonds%20violated%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information%20and%20were%20thus%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20asked%20the%20SBI%20to%20provide%20data%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20and%20encashed%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019%20to%20the%20ECI%20by%20March%206%2C%20although%20the%20bank%20did%20so%20only%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20the%20court%20rejected%20its%20request%20for%20extra%20time%20till%20the%20end%20of%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eci.gov.in%2Fdisclosure-of-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Euploaded%20two%20sets%20of%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20file%20contains%20the%20details%20of%20companies%20that%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20the%20other%20file%20contains%20a%20list%20of%20political%20parties%20that%20encashed%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20data%20published%20by%20the%20ECI%20on%20Thursday%20gives%20a%20clear%20picture%20of%20the%20corporations%20and%20private%20business%20houses%20that%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20between%202019%20and%202024%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20provide%20any%20information%20on%20which%20party%20redeemed%20the%20bonds%20of%20what%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20in%20contravention%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20that%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme.%20The%20court%20clearly%20observed%20that%20the%20opacity%20surrounding%20the%20political%20donations%20could%20be%20the%20basis%20of%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangements%20between%20companies%20and%20political%20parties%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20electoral%20bonds%20contained%20a%20unique%20identification%20number%20%E2%80%93%20or%20what%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunique%20matching%20code%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20could%20be%20used%20to%20match%20each%20donor%20to%20the%20beneficiary%20political%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%2C%20the%20SBI%20could%20have%20easily%20furnished%20details%20about%20which%20political%20party%20redeemed%20which%20bonds%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20top%20court%20had%20ended%20the%20controversial%20scheme%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20the%20data%20uploaded%20makes%20it%20rather%20difficult%20to%20infer%20whether%20there%20were%20any%20quid%20pro%20quo%20dealings%20between%20companies%20which%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20different%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20whether%20the%20SBI%20will%20furnish%20these%20details%20soon%20or%20if%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20intervene%20in%20the%C2%A0matter%C2%A0again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20also%20questioned%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20motivations%20given%20that%20it%20promptly%20handed%20over%20the%20data%20on%20Tuesday%20despite%20it%20asking%20for%20three%20months%E2%80%99%20extra%20time%20just%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20files%20shared%20by%20the%20SBI%20expose%20a%20close%20nexus%20between%20corporations%20and%20political%20parties%2C%20especially%20the%20ruling%20BJP%2C%20which%20has%20received%20the%20maximum%20donations%20of%20any%20party%20from%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nexus%20was%20well-known%20but%20is%20now%20backed%20by%20solid%20data%2C%20even%20though%20the%20SBI%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20bank%2C%20has%20attempted%20to%20retain%20a%20layer%20of%20darkness%20around%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EECI%20seeks%20modification%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20order%2C%20says%20advocate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20posted%20on%20social%20media%20that%20the%20ECI%20has%20also%20filed%20%E2%80%9Can%20application%20to%20modify%20the%20SC%20%5BSupreme%20Court%5D%20order%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%E2%80%9D%20and%20alleged%20that%20after%20the%20SBI%20tried%20to%20hide%20information%20by%20moving%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20ECI%20was%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20the%20SBI%20and%20ECI%20of%20acting%20like%20%E2%80%9Ccaged%20parrots%E2%80%9D%20to%20protect%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20which%20is%20%E2%80%9Cdesperate%20to%20hide%20information%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBJP%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20analysis%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20revealed%20that%20the%20BJP%20received%20nearly%20Rs%206%2C565%20crore%20or%2055%25%20of%20the%20total%20funds%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20March%202018%20and%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20national%20rival%2C%20the%20Congress%2C%20garnered%20a%20mere%209.3%25%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2016%2C518.11%20crore%20donated%20to%20political%20parties%20through%20the%20bonds%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remaining%20amount%20was%20shared%20by%20other%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20February%20order%2C%20the%20SBI%20was%20asked%20to%20include%20in%20its%20disclosure%20the%20date%20bonds%20were%20purchased%20on%2C%20their%20denominations%20and%20the%20names%20of%20those%20who%20purchased%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20ordered%20for%20data%20on%20every%20electoral%20bond%20encashed%20by%20political%20parties%20since%20April%2012%2C%202019%20to%20be%20furnished%2C%20including%20the%20date%20they%20were%20encashed%20on%20and%20the%20bonds%E2%80%99%20denominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20before%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20original%20deadline%2C%20the%20SBI%20said%20it%20would%20need%20time%20till%20June%2030%20this%20year%20because%20it%20had%20to%20compile%2044%2C434%20sets%20of%20information%20from%20two%20%E2%80%98silos%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20court%20asked%20the%20bank%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20data%20by%20March%206%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20may%20proceed%20against%20the%20bank%20on%20grounds%20on%20wilful%20disobedience%20if%20it%20did%20not%20meet%20this%20new%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20developing%20story.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710427817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15125309%2FNirvachan-Sadan-TW.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-uploads-electoral-bonds-data%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20nature%20of%20the%20data%20uploaded%20to%20the%20ECI's%20website%20makes%20it%20rather%20difficult%20to%20infer%20whether%20there%20were%20any%20quid%20pro%20quo%20dealings%20between%20companies%20which%20bought%20the%20bonds%20and%20different%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-uploads-electoral-bonds-data%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20are%20the%20New%20Election%20Commissioner-Appointees%2C%20Sukhbir%20Singh%20Sandhu%20and%20Gyanesh%20Kumar%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06152712%2FElection-Commission-of-India-Photo-PTI1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20committee%20headed%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20picked%20two%20retired%20Indian%20Administrative%20Service%20(IAS)%20officers%20%E2%80%93%20Sukhbir%20Singh%20Sandhu%20and%20Gyanesh%20Kumar%20%E2%80%93%20as%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs).%20They%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20sworn%20in%20tomorrow%20(March%2015)%2C%20according%20to%20a%20gazette%20notification%20issued%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20meeting%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20was%20held%20at%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20residence%20on%20Thursday%20(March%2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20appointments%20have%20come%20just%20days%20before%20a%20schedule%20for%20the%20general%20elections%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contravention%20of%20the%20guidelines%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20Anoop%20Banarwal%20judgment%20of%20March%202%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnew-bill-selection-of-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Ewas%20not%20in%20the%20panel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20on%20the%20committee%20to%20pick%20two%20ECs%20were%20his%20senior%20party%20colleague%20and%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Adhir%20Chowdhury%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20Opposition%20party%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20minutes%20after%20the%20meeting%20ended%2C%20Choudhury%20stated%20publicly%20that%20he%20was%20neither%20given%20adequate%20time%20to%20look%20at%20the%20profile%20of%20the%20candidates%20for%20the%20post%20nor%20given%20the%20list%20of%20the%20shortlisted%20names.%20The%20entire%20list%20of%20212%20candidates%20was%20handed%20over%20to%20him%20just%20a%20day%20before%20the%20meeting%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20it%20implies%20that%20the%20candidates%20were%20shortlisted%20between%20Modi%20and%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20PM-led%20committee%20announced%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20ECs%20just%20a%20day%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20to%20hear%20a%20petition%20challenging%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20committee%20itself%20on%20grounds%20of%20its%20stranglehold%20over%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20has%20raised%20questions%20regarding%20the%20urgency%20displayed%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20party%20(BJP)-led%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20ECs%20are%20scheduled%20to%20take%20the%20oath%20tomorrow%20morning%20(March%2015)%2C%20while%20the%20matter%20will%20also%20be%20heard%20on%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Gyanesh%20Kumar%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20retired%20IAS%20officer%20of%20the%20Kerala%20cadre%2C%20Gyanesh%20Kumar%20belongs%20to%20the%201988%20batch.%20Kumar%20has%20worked%20closely%20with%20Shah%2C%20both%20as%20minister%20of%20home%20affairs%20and%20as%20the%20minister%20of%20cooperatives.%20Kumar%20also%20worked%20as%20the%20parliamentary%20affairs%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20has%20been%20the%20key%20person%20for%20a%20number%20of%20significant%20moves%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20had%20embarked%20on%20after%20its%20return%20to%20power%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*As%20joint%20secretary%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20desk%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20Kumar%20worked%20closely%20with%20Amit%20Shah%20in%20the%20transition%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20into%20a%20Union%20Territory%20in%20August%202019.%20He%20was%20an%20active%20participant%20in%20the%20preparation%20of%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Reorganisation%20Bill%2C%20which%20then%20became%20an%20Act.%20The%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20was%20the%20first%20massive%20decision%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20took%20after%20its%20return%20to%20power%20in%202019.%20Shah%20became%20the%20home%20minister%20in%202019%20replacing%20Rajnath%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*After%20the%20successful%20completion%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20project%2C%20Kumar%2C%20in%20January%202020%2C%20was%20deputed%20by%20Shah%20to%20the%20Ayodhya%20desk%20at%20the%20MHA.%20As%20the%20head%20of%20this%20desk%2C%20he%20oversaw%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20Trust%20to%20build%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20in%20Ayodhya.%20The%20consecration%20of%20the%20temple%2C%20built%20under%20the%20watch%20of%20that%20Trust%2C%20was%20carried%20out%20by%20Modi%20on%20January%2022%2C%20an%20occasion%20being%20used%20by%20Modi-Shah%20and%20their%20party%20to%20garner%20votes%20in%20the%20ensuing%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Around%20the%20time%20Modi%20inaugurated%20the%20temple%20at%20Ayodhya%2C%20Kumar%20retired%20from%20service.%20After%20heading%20the%20Ayodhya%20desk%2C%20he%20was%20dispatched%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20affairs%20ministry%20as%20its%20secretary%20in%20April%202021.%20One%20of%20the%20major%20aberrations%20noticed%20during%20that%20period%20in%20parliament%20was%20a%20blanket%20ban%20%E2%80%93%20first%20ever%20%E2%80%93%20on%20journalists%20with%20government%20accreditation%20to%20cover%20the%20sessions.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20time%20the%20Modi%20government%20was%20constructing%20the%20new%20parliament%20building%20and%20the%20Central%20Vista%20area%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20%E2%80%98Naya%20Bharat%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Modi%20inaugurated%20the%20new%20parliament%20building%2C%20Kumar%2C%20often%20termed%20as%20one%20of%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20right-hand%20man%20in%20the%20power%20corridors%20of%20Delhi%2C%20was%20sent%20to%20another%20ministry.%20This%20ministry%20is%20also%20headed%20by%20Shah%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Cooperation.%20In%20May%202022%2C%20Kumar%20became%20secretary%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20retiring%20from%20service%20in%20January%2C%20Kumar%20had%20put%20together%20three%20cooperative%20societies%20within%20the%20ministry%2C%20a%20flagship%20project%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%20his%20tenure%2C%20the%20cooperation%20ministry%20saw%20enactment%20of%20the%20Multi-State%20Cooperative%20Societies%20(MSCS)%20(Amendment)%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20and%20formation%20of%20three%20new%20national%20cooperative%20bodies%20%E2%80%94%20Bharatiya%20Beej%20Sahakari%20Samiti%20Limited%20(BBSSL)%2C%20National%20Cooperative%20Organics%20Limited%20(NCOL)%2C%20and%20National%20Cooperative%20Export%20Limited%20(NCEL).%20He%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20the%20timely%20launch%20of%20the%20CRCS-Sahara%20refund%20portal%20for%20submission%20of%20claims%20by%20genuine%20depositors%20of%20four%20Multi-State%20Cooperative%20Societies%20of%20Sahara%20Group%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20after%20the%20news%20spread%20about%20his%20name%20as%20one%20of%20the%20election%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20a%20day%20before%20Kumar%20was%20reportedly%20picked%20by%20the%20committee%20to%20the%20post%2C%20Shah%20inaugurated%20a%20new%20office%20to%20unroll%20the%20work%20that%20was%20to%20be%20carried%20out%20under%20those%20cooperative%20societies.%20He%20called%20them%20a%20panacea%20to%20%E2%80%9Csolve%20many%20problems%20of%20Indian%20agriculture%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20they%20would%20%E2%80%9Cenhance%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20by%20promoting%20exports%20of%20farm%20products%2C%20including%20organic%20foods.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Press%20Information%20Bureau%20note%20said%2C%20while%20inaugurating%20the%20office%2C%20%E2%80%9CShah%20mentioned%20that%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Shri%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20we%20are%20moving%20ahead%20with%20the%20vision%20of%20%E2%80%98Sahakar%20se%20Samriddhi%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20S.S.%20Sandhu%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandhu%2C%20another%20retired%20IAS%20officer%20from%20the%201988%20batch%2C%20happens%20to%20be%20a%20batchmate%20of%20Kumar%2C%20from%20the%20Uttarakhand%20cadre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20being%20sent%20back%20to%20Uttarakhand%20to%20take%20over%20as%20the%20chief%20secretary%20in%20July%202021%2C%20Sandhu%20was%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20National%20Highways%20Authority%20of%20India%20(NHAI).%20He%20took%20over%20the%20reins%20of%20the%20NHAI%20in%20October%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandhu%20was%20instrumental%20in%20carrying%20out%20some%20of%20the%20key%20road%20projects%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20including%20constructing%20a%20record%20number%20of%20highways.%20This%20accomplishment%20of%20NHAI%20under%20Sandhu%20has%20been%20a%20key%20party%20campaign%20highlight.%20Modi%20has%20been%20seen%20inaugurating%20highways%20to%20showcase%20that%20the%20NHAI%E2%80%99s%20achievement%20is%20actually%20because%20of%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandhu%20was%20to%20retire%20as%20Uttarakhand%20chief%20secretary%20in%20July%202023.%20However%2C%20he%20was%20given%20a%20six-month%20extension%20because%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ongoing%20works%20at%20Kedarnath%20and%20Badrinath%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20number%20of%20key%20projects%20funded%20by%20the%20Centre%20that%20are%20underway%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Fchief-secy-ss-sandhu-gets-6-month-extension%2Farticleshow%2F102027337.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20projects%20around%20the%20Hindu%20pilgrimage%20sites%20of%20Badrinath%20and%20Kedarnath%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20flagship%20initiatives%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.narendramodi.in%2Fprime-minister-narendra-modi-to-visit-kedarnath-and-badrinath-on-21st-october-565210%5C%22%3Evisit%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Badrinath%20and%20Kedarnath%20in%20October%202021%20to%20launch%20those%20projects%20made%20headlines.%20Sandhu%20oversaw%20those%20projects%20at%20the%20state%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710427429000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F06152712%2FElection-Commission-of-India-Photo-PTI1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwho-are-the-new-election-commissioner-appointees-sukhbir-singh-sandhu-and-gyanesh-kumar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kumar%20and%20Sandhu%20are%20retired%20IAS%20batchmates.%20Kumar%20has%20been%20key%20to%20several%20home%20ministry%20projects%20and%20also%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20Trust.%20Before%20being%20sent%20back%20to%20Uttarakhand%20to%20take%20over%20as%20the%20chief%20secretary%20in%20July%202021%2C%20Sandhu%20was%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20NHAI.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwho-are-the-new-election-commissioner-appointees-sukhbir-singh-sandhu-and-gyanesh-kumar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Japan's%20same-sex%20marriage%20ban%20ruled%20unconstitutional%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710426360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-japan-same-sex-marriage_6490219.png%3F20240314145435%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fjapans-same-sex-marriage-ban-ruled-unconstitutional-13094598%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20high%20court%20in%20Japan%20has%20ruled%20that%20the%20country's%20ban%20on%20same-sex%20marriage%20is%20unconstitutional.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fjapans-same-sex-marriage-ban-ruled-unconstitutional-13094598%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fjapans-same-sex-marriage-ban-ruled-unconstitutional-13094598%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fjapans-same-sex-marriage-ban-ruled-unconstitutional-13094598%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lullabies%20to%20Languages%3A%20Fellowship%20Offers%20Funds%20to%20Help%20Tribal%20Youth%20Preserve%20Generational%20Wisdom%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20published%20in%20partnership%20with%20Samvaad%20%E2%80%93%20Enabled%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2050%20years%2C%20India%20has%20lost%20over%20250%20languages%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20UNESCO.%20This%20loss%20not%20only%20affects%20languages%20but%20also%20various%20fields%20like%20history%2C%20biology%2C%20and%20anthropology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20good%20news.%20Lately%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20growing%20effort%20to%20preserve%20cultural%20identities%20throughout%20India%2C%20and%20the%20Samvaad%20Fellowship%20programme%20stands%20as%20a%20significant%20contributor%20to%20this%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20in%202017%20to%20empower%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344574%2Ftata-samvaad-tribal-conclave-preserves-lost-heritage-artisans-sell-handicrafts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etribal%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20fellowship%20encourages%20their%20youth%20to%20document%20their%20history%2C%20culture%2C%20ecology%2C%20traditions%2C%20art%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20purpose%20of%20the%20fellowship%20is%20to%20get%20tribal%20communities%20to%20deep%20dive%20into%20their%20culture%20and%20help%20them%20shape%20their%20ideas%20in%20collaboration%20with%20various%20experts.%20The%20idea%20behind%20documenting%20different%20cultures%20is%20to%20create%20a%20repository%20of%20information%20and%20make%20it%20accessible%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20At%20Samvaad%2C%20being%20a%20tribal%20is%20a%20source%20of%20pride.%20The%20community%20answers%20the%20toughest%20questions%20about%20their%20identity%20and%20tries%20to%20address%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sourav%20Roy%2C%20TSF%20CEO%2C%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fellowship%20is%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F344526%2Fsamvaad-tata-steel-foundation-celebrates-culture-of-tribes-of-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESamvaad%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20tribal%20conclaves%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%2C%20enabled%20by%20Tata%20Steel%20Foundation%20(TSF).%20It%20takes%20place%20from%2015%20to%2019%20November%20every%20year%20to%20commemorate%20the%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20Birsa%20Munda%2C%20a%20tribal%20independence%20activist%20and%20leader%20from%20Jharkhand%E2%80%99s%20Munda%20tribe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamvaad%20stepped%20into%20a%20decadal%20journey%20in%202023%20and%20the%20recent%20edition%E2%80%99s%20theme%20was%20%E2%80%98Walk%20with%20Me%E2%80%99.%20The%20theme%20recognised%20the%20journey%20of%20ideas%2C%20dialogues%2C%20individuals%2C%20and%20collectives%20within%20and%20among%20the%20tribes%20of%20India%2C%20aiming%20to%20address%20future%20challenges%20through%20shared%20wisdom%2C%20idea%20exchange%2C%20and%20self-learning.%20The%20five-day%20conclave%20spotlighted%20various%20solution-driven%20dialogues%20and%20initiatives%20that%20have%20emerged%20from%20past%20conclaves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hosted%20at%20five%20locations%20%E2%80%94%20TSF%20Community%20Hall%20(RD%20Bhatta)%2C%20Jamshedpur%20Nature%20Trail%2C%20Tribal%20Cultural%20Centre%2C%20Gopal%20Maidan%2C%20and%20Johar%20Haat.%20Gopal%20Maidan%20and%20Tribal%20Culture%20Centre%20served%20as%20the%20main%20activity%20hubs%20while%20Johar%20Haat%20housed%20a%20cloud%20kitchen%20facility%20for%20preparing%20food%20for%20home%20delivery%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Zomato.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20conclave%20has%20celebrated%20and%20united%20over%2040%2C000%20people%20from%20over%20200%20tribes%20in%20India%20and%2017%20other%20countries.%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20past%20fellows%20%E2%80%94%20Banwang%20Losu%20and%20Amabel%20Susngi%20%E2%80%94%20about%20their%20tremendous%20action%20towards%20preserving%20their%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20fellowship%20aims%20to%20engage%20tribal%20communities%20in%20exploring%20their%20culture%20and%20collaboratively%20shaping%20their%20ideas%20with%20experts.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FWancho_language_training_of_teacher_PC_banwang_losu-1710425245-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344889%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20fellowship%20aims%20to%20engage%20tribal%20communities%20in%20exploring%20their%20culture%20and%20collaboratively%20shaping%20their%20ideas%20with%20experts.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPreserving%20lullabies%20and%20languages%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20centuries%2C%20people%20across%20the%20world%20have%20followed%20the%20nightly%20ritual%20of%20singing%20lullabies%20to%20infants%20for%20a%20peaceful%20sleep.%20Closer%20home%2C%20we%20have%20thousands%20of%20lullabies%20in%20different%20languages.%20However%2C%20this%20tradition%20has%20faded%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsk%20yourself%20whether%20you%20remember%20a%20lullaby%20from%20your%20childhood!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%2028-year-old%20Amabel%20Susngi%20from%20Meghalaya%20observed%20that%20the%20lullabies%20in%20her%20native%20language%20Khasi%20were%20becoming%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20document%20them.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20Samvaad%20Fellowship%2C%20she%20gathered%20various%20lullabies%20and%20published%20them%20in%20a%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20PhD%20researcher%20and%20a%20singer%2C%20she%20travelled%20across%20Meghalaya%20for%20over%20a%20year%20to%20collect%20these%20lullabies.%20She%20has%20documented%2025%20of%20them%20in%20her%20book%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHa%20Yupiam%20Ka%20Bei%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(On%20Mother%E2%80%99s%20Lap)%2C%20which%20was%20published%20in%20both%20Khasi%20and%20English%20this%20year%20at%20Samvaad.%20It%20also%20comes%20with%20musical%20notations%2C%20and%20each%20piece%20has%20a%20QR%20code%20leading%20the%20reader%20to%20its%20YouTube%20version.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20researching%20the%20folk%20music%20of%20the%20Pnar%20community%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20not%20many%20people%20remembered%20lullabies.%20That%20was%20a%20shock.%20Lullabies%20have%20been%20passed%20down%20through%20generations.%20Whether%20traditional%20or%20something%20made%20up%20by%20parents%2C%20it%20has%20been%20an%20important%20fabric%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amabel%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20road%20to%20publishing%20had%20its%20challenges%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20the%20biggest%20being%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CParents%20don%E2%80%99t%20sing%20anymore%2C%20and%20elderly%20people%20do%20not%20quite%20remember%20all%20the%20lullabies.%20Some%20knew%20only%20one%20line%20or%20two%2C%20and%20some%20remembered%20only%20the%20tune%20or%20lyrics.%20Scheduling%20meetings%20was%20not%20an%20option%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20work%20around%20their%20availability.%20Samvaad%20solved%20the%20critical%20funding%20problem%2C%20and%20it%20helped%20me%20connect%20with%20other%20fellows%20around%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Banwang%20Losu%20from%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20developed%20a%20script%20to%20preserve%20Wancho%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Tibetan-Burman%20language%20spoken%20in%20the%20Longding%20region%20of%20the%20state%20and%20some%20parts%20of%20Myanmar%2C%20Nagaland%2C%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20first%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20have%20a%20Wancho%20script%20when%20he%20was%20asked%20to%20collect%20data%20about%20his%20community%20as%20part%20of%20his%20socio-economic%20study%20in%20college.%20He%20was%20unable%20to%20find%20the%20right%20English%20words%20to%20convey%20subtle%20tones.%20He%20tried%20to%20do%20some%20research%20and%20even%20started%20pursuing%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20in%20linguistics%20at%20Deccan%20College%20Post%20Graduation%20and%20Research%20Institute%20in%20Pune.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20developing%20the%20script%2C%20he%20took%20inspiration%20from%20nature%20and%20Wancho%20cultural%20symbols%2C%20practices%2C%20and%20gestures.%20He%20developed%20a%20script%20with%2044%20letters%20(15%20vowels%20and%2029%20consonants)%2C%20each%20letter%20representing%20a%20distinct%20tone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20was%20the%20first%20fellow%20at%20Samvaad.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20working%20on%20the%20Wancho%20script%2C%20I%20heard%20about%20Samvaad%20and%20came%20here%20in%202017%20without%20any%20proposal.%20However%2C%20the%20jury%20was%20delighted%20to%20see%20my%20work.%20Being%20a%20fellow%20here%20was%20eye-opening%20as%20it%20is%20the%20only%20programme%20for%20tribals%20at%20this%20scale.%20Using%20the%20grant%2C%20I%20made%20textbooks%20on%20the%20Wancho%20language%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanwang%20taught%20the%20language%20to%202%2C000%20people%2C%20and%2020%20of%20them%20are%20now%20teachers.%20Thanks%20to%20his%20work%2C%20over%206%2C000%20students%20can%20read%20and%20write%20in%20Wancho.%20He%20also%20got%20the%20script%20approved%20for%20online%20use%20by%20the%20US-based%20Unicode%20Consortium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20language%20is%20equally%20important%20irrespective%20of%20how%20big%20or%20small.%20We%20have%20to%20look%20at%20other%20minority%20languages%20with%20the%20same%20status%20and%20build%20scripts%20to%20preserve%20them.%20Loss%20of%20language%20is%20a%20loss%20of%20our%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202560px)%20100vw%2C%202560px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-scaled.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20year%2C%20out%20of%2035%20applicants%2C%2010%20were%20awarded%20the%20fellowship%20following%20thorough%20rounds%20of%20interviews%20and%20pitches.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-scaled.jpg%202560w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-1536x864.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-2048x1152.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FSourav_Roy_taking_a_session_with_fellowship_applicants_11zon-1710425242-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20cl